						               													<description>&amp;quot;Sagas of Mistal&amp;quot; is a 4X strategy game happening in a classic medieval fantasy theme, combining Area-control opposition, Economic, Auction and Building mechanics, with complex victory conditions (a kind of Civilization game, where there are multiple ways of winning).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A game is lasting about 120 minutes and can be played by 4 players (possibly less or more with other maps). The original intended target audience was the expert gamers, but after heaps of blind tests, it seems to have a wider audience than expected (family+).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;We believe the hooks of this game are the following:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Replay value: it's a rich, balanced and complex game, with many options of play&amp;#10;     Intuitive and friendly: rules are quite easy to get, the prototype's design is catchy&amp;#10;     Fun and cognitive: an area-control and economic game with dice, which is &amp;quot;telling stories&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The project is two years old, and has been playtested over 250 times (private sessions, blind tests, game festivals, game bars..). We value balancing and testing a lot, and we reckon this game has a good potential for editing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designers&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
